menu "WellD Sensor"

    config WELLD_SENSOR_ADC_CHANNEL
        int "ADC1 channel for 4-20 mA sensor"
        default 0
        range 0 6

    config WELLD_SENSOR_SHUNT_MILLIOHMS
        int "Shunt resistor value (milliohms)"
        default 100000
        range 1000 155000
        help
            Value in milliohms. 100000 = 100 Ω → 4 mA gives 0.40 V, 20 mA gives 2.00 V.
            Upper bound is 155 Ω (155000 mΩ): at 20 mA full scale that produces 3.1 V,
            the top of the ADC linear range. Higher values exceed the ESP32-C6 ADC
            absolute-maximum input of 3.6 V and will damage the GPIO pin.

    config WELLD_SENSOR_MAX_DEPTH_CM
        int "Maximum well depth (centimeters)"
        default 600
        help
            Depth at 20 mA (full-scale output of the transducer). 600 = 6 m.

    config WELLD_SENSOR_OFFSET_CM
        int "Water level offset (centimeters, signed)"
        default 0
        range -600 600
        help
            Added to the computed level after scaling. Use a negative value
            when the transducer sits below the true zero reference point
            (e.g. -50 if it hangs 50 cm below the water outlet pipe).
            Can be overridden at runtime via NVS key "welld/offset_cm".
            Both this default and any runtime value written to NVS key
            'welld/offset_cm' are clamped to the range -600 to +600 cm at
            runtime.

    config WELLD_BATT_ADC_CHANNEL
        int "ADC1 channel for battery voltage (set to -1 to disable)"
        default -1
        range -1 6
        help
            ADC1 channel wired to the battery via a resistor divider.
            Set to -1 to disable battery monitoring.

    config WELLD_BATT_DIVIDER_RATIO
        int "Battery divider ratio * 100 (e.g. 200 = 2:1 divider)"
        default 200
        range 136 1000
        help
            If your divider halves the voltage (R1=R2), enter 200 (2.00x).
            Reported voltage = ADC voltage * ratio / 100.
            Minimum is 136 (1.36:1), which maps a 4.2 V Li-ion full charge to
            3.09 V at the ADC pin — just inside the 3.1 V linear range. Lower
            ratios put the raw battery voltage on the ADC input and risk
            exceeding the 3.6 V absolute maximum. For 12 V SLA use ratio >= 465.
            Used for the ADS1115 AIN2 divider fallback when MAX17048 is absent.

    config WELLD_BATT_FULL_MV
        int "Battery full voltage (mV)"
        default 4200
        range 3000 5000
        help
            Voltage read at 100 % state of charge. 4200 = LiPo/Li-ion.
            Used by the Z2M converter; also used by the firmware as the
            threshold below which Zigbee sends and NVS writes are skipped
            to protect a nearly-dead cell from brown-out during TX.

    config WELLD_BATT_EMPTY_MV
        int "Battery empty voltage (mV)"
        default 3000
        range 2000 4000
        help
            Voltage read at 0 % state of charge. 3000 = LiPo/Li-ion cutoff.
            When battery voltage (from MAX17048 or ADC divider) drops at or
            below this threshold, the device skips the Zigbee send and all
            NVS writes and sleeps for the maximum interval to conserve charge.

    config WELLD_DS18B20_GPIO
        int "GPIO number for DS18B20 data line"
        default 7
        range 0 21
        help
            GPIO connected to the DS18B20 data pin via a 4.7 kΩ pull-up to 3.3 V.
            External power mode is required: connect DS18B20 VCC to 3.3 V and GND
            to GND. Parasite-power mode (VCC pin tied to GND) is not supported —
            the RMT one-wire driver does not drive a strong pull-up during
            conversion, so a parasite-powered sensor will stall and return an
            out-of-range reading that is silently discarded every wakeup.

    config WELLD_I2C_SDA_GPIO
        int "I2C SDA GPIO (ADS1115 + MAX17048)"
        range 0 21
        default 10
        help
            GPIO number for the shared I2C SDA line. Used by ADS1115 (16-bit
            ADC, 0x48) and MAX17048 (fuel gauge, 0x36).

    config WELLD_I2C_SCL_GPIO
        int "I2C SCL GPIO (ADS1115 + MAX17048)"
        range 0 21
        default 11
        help
            GPIO number for the shared I2C SCL line.

    config WELLD_VLOOP_GPIO
        int "VLOOP 12 V boost enable GPIO (TPS61023 EN)"
        range 0 21
        default 5
        help
            Drive HIGH before any 4-20 mA transducer read; allow 5 ms soft-start;
            drive LOW immediately after. Max ON time 100 ms per wake cycle.

    config WELLD_BATT_DIV_EN_GPIO
        int "Battery divider enable GPIO (Q2 gate)"
        range 0 21
        default 15
        help
            Drives Q2 gate (BSS123). HIGH enables the resistor divider connected
            to ADS1115 AIN2. Drive HIGH for 1 ms before reading; LOW after.
            Only used as fallback when MAX17048 is unavailable.

    config WELLD_ADS1115_DRDY_GPIO
        int "ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY GPIO"
        range 0 21
        default 12
        help
            GPIO connected to the ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY open-drain output. The
            sensor component configures the ADS1115 in conversion-ready mode
            (Lo_thresh = 0x8000, Hi_thresh = 0x7FFF per datasheet) so the pin
            pulses LOW when each single-shot conversion completes. The GPIO is
            configured as input with the ESP32-C6 internal pull-up enabled
            (ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY is open-drain). A falling-edge ISR releases a
            binary semaphore so the sensor task can block instead of polling.
            Timeout fallback of 10 ms protects against a missing edge.

endmenu
